3	/**
4	 * HOST-PARSE gate: the host-substring class dies here (GAPS.md `host-substring`, caution.md C-009).
5	 *
6	 * "Is this URL on this site" must be decided by PARSING the URL and comparing the HOSTNAME, never by a
7	 * substring/token test. `url.includes(domain)` is TRUE for https://evil.com/linkedin.com; `host.endsWith
8	 * (domain)` is TRUE for notreed.co.uk vs reed.co.uk. The old estate bound the wrong company's identity
9	 * and the wrong country's law off exactly these. The ONE door is tools/lib/safe-fetch.js (isSameHost /
10	 * sameRegistrableSite / registrableDomain / hostOf); this gate fails CI on any host comparison done by
11	 * substring OUTSIDE that door.
12	 *
13	 * DETECTION (acorn AST): a string-search call - .includes / .indexOf / .search / .match / .startsWith /
14	 * .endsWith - whose FIRST argument is host-ish:
15	 *   - an identifier named domain/dom/host/hostname/site/registrable/apex/fqdn, or
16	 *   - a member expression ending .hostname/.host/.domain, or
17	 *   - a bare-hostname string literal (linkedin.com, reed.co.uk).
18	 * A scheme check (u.indexOf('://'), href.startsWith('/')) and a dot check (h.includes('.')) are NOT
19	 * host-substring: their argument is not a host, so they are spared. Comparing PARSED hostnames
20	 * (new URL(u).hostname === domain) never appears as a string-search call, so it is spared too.
21	 *
22	 * Engine: acorn is MANDATORY (ships transitively via eslint). Without it the gate REFUSES (exit 2) rather
23	 * than approximate - under-reporting a host-substring is an unearned zero (Constitution Rule 4). A string
24	 * literal that merely CONTAINS `.includes(` is invisible to acorn, so no false hit from comments/strings.
25	 *
26	 * Modes (tools/lib/gate-cli.js dialect):
27	 *   node tools/domain-gates/host-parse.js               scan the engine source, exit 1 on any violation
28	 *   node tools/domain-gates/host-parse.js --json <path> also write findings JSON for the sweep normaliser
29	 *   node tools/domain-gates/host-parse.js --calibrate   scan eval/calibration-known-bad/fixtures/ and
30	 *                                                        REQUIRE the seeded host-substring to be caught
